<item>
            <title>[LU-7516] Issue in mounting Lustre File system in Client</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7516</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;File system mount issue on client after mounting MDT &amp;amp; OST successfully&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@akash01 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# mount -t lustre 172.16.101.57@o2ib:172.16.101.58@o2ib:/lustre02 /sachome&lt;br/&gt;
mount.lustre: mount 172.16.101.57@o2ib:172.16.101.58@o2ib:/lustre02 at /sachome failed: Invalid argument&lt;br/&gt;
This may have multiple causes.&lt;br/&gt;
Is &apos;lustre02&apos; the correct filesystem name?&lt;br/&gt;
Are the mount options correct?&lt;br/&gt;
Check the syslog for more info.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
